OL,6,FHeadline sequences will be axed, with
OL,7,Flive news programmes going straight
OL,8,Fto the top story of the hour.
OL,10,FThe combined daytime schedule will
OL,11,Fbroadcast from Studio E (the main
OL,12,Fnewsroom-facing studio) until April,
OL,13,Fwhen Studio C (the current World News
OL,14,Fstudio in the basement) will take
OL,15,Fover full time.
OL,17,FBBC Sport in Salford will produce a
OL,18,Fmix of combined and UK-only sports
OL,19,Fbulletins.
OL,21,FIn an e-mail to staff, BBC Deputy
OL,22,FNews Editor Toby Castle confirmed:
OL,3,CJoint UK/international BBC News
OL,4,Cservice from March
